]]\n|-\n|DF ||'''15'''||{{flagicon|BRA}} [[Alex Sandro Pinho|Alex Pinho]]\n|-\n|DF ||'''17'''||{{flagicon|BRA}} [[V\u00e1lber Roel de Oliveira|V\u00e1lber]] || || {{subon|89}}\n|-\n|DF ||'''31'''||{{flagicon|BRA}} [[Claudemir V\u00edtor|V\u00edtor]] || || {{subon|81}}\n|-\n|MF ||'''18'''||{{flagicon|BRA}} [[N\u00e9lson Domingues de Ara\u00fajo|N\u00e9lson]]\n|-\n|FW ||'''20'''||{{flagicon|BRA}} [[Maur\u00edcio Poggi Villela|Mauricinho]]\n|-\n|FW ||'''23'''||{{flagicon|BRA}} [[Guilherme de C\u00e1ssio Alves|Guilherme]] || || {{subon|86}}\n|-\n|colspan=3|'''Manager:'''\n|-\n|colspan=4|{{flagicon|BRA}} [[Ant\u00f4nio Lopes]]\n|}\n|}\n{| style=\"width:100%; font-size:90%\"\n|\n'''Man of the Match:'''\n<br />{{flagicon|ESP}} [[Ra\u00fal (footballer)|Ra\u00fal]] (Real Madrid)<ref>[https://web.archive.org/web/20010513122633/http://toyotacup.com/html/history/19/g_ef.html Toyota Cup]</ref>\n\n'''[[Assistant referee (association football)|Assistant referees]]:'''\n<br />{{flagicon|MAS}} Halim Abdul Hamid ([[Football Association of Malaysia|Malaysia]])\n<br />{{flagicon|JPN|1947}} Keiji Kamiara ([[Japan Football Association|Japan]])\n<br />'''[[Assistant referee (association football)#Fourth official|Fourth official]]:'''\n<br />{{flagicon|JPN|1947}} Hiroyuki Umemoto ([[Japan Football Association|Japan]])\n|style=\"width:60%; vertical-align:top;\"|\n'''Match rules'''\n*90 minutes.\n*30 minutes of [[golden goal]] [[Overtime (sports)#Association football|extra time]] if necessary.\n*[[Penalty shoot-out (association football)|Penalty shoot-out]] if scores still level.\n*Seven named substitutes.\n*Maximum of three substitutions.\n|}\n\n==See also==\n*[[1997\u201398 UEFA Champions League]]\n*[[1998 Copa Libertadores]]\n*[[Real Madrid CF in international football competitions]]\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*[https://web.archive.org/web/20080702021743/http://www.fifa.com/classicfootball/clubs/matchreport/newsid%3D512289.html FIFA Article] (Archived)\n*[http://www.conmebol.com/articulos_ver.jsp?id=3593&slangab=S Copa Europea/Sudamericana - Toyota: Real Madrid 2 - Vasco da Gama 1], [[CONMEBOL]].com\n\n{{Intercontinental Cup (football)}}\n{{Real Madrid CF matches}}\n{{CR Vasco da Gama matches}}\n\n[[Category:1998\u201399 in European football|Intercontinental Cup]]\n[[Category:1998 in South American football|Intercontinental Cup]]\n[[Category:1998 in Japanese football|Intercontinental Cup]]\n[[Category:Intercontinental Cup (football)|1998]]\n[[Category:Real Madrid CF matches|Intercontinental Cup 1998]]\n[[Category:CR Vasco da Gama matches|Intercontinental Cup 1998]]\n[[Category:Intercontinental Cup (football) matches hosted by Japan]]\n[[Category:1998\u201399 in Spanish football|Intercontinental Cup]]\n[[Category:1998 in Brazilian football|Intercontinental Cup]]\n[[Category:December 1998 sports events in Asia]]\n[[Category:Sports competitions in Tokyo]]\n[[Category:1998 in Tokyo]]\n\n{{Footy-competition-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{Use dmy dates|date=April 2020}}\n{{Infobox football match\n|              title = 1998 Intercontinental Cup\n| image = ToyotaCup1998.jpg\n|            caption = Match programme cover\n|              team1 = [[Real Madrid C.F.|Real Madrid]]\n|   team1association = {{flagicon|ESP|size=30px}}\n|         team1score = 2\n|              team2 = [[CR Vasco da Gama|Vasco da Gama]]\n|   team2association = {{flagicon|BRA|size=30px}}\n|         team2score = 1\n|               date = 1 December 1998\n|            stadium = [[National Stadium (Tokyo)|National Stadium]]\n|               city = [[Tokyo]]\n| man_of_the_match1a = [[Ra\u00fal (footballer)|Ra\u00fal]] ([[Real Madrid C.F.|Real Madrid]])\n|            referee = [[Mario S\u00e1nchez Yanten|Mario S\u00e1nchez]] ([[Football Federation of Chile|Chile]])\n|         attendance = 51,514\n|            weather = Clear night<br />{{convert|14.6|\u00b0C|\u00b0F}}<br />68% [[humidity]]\n|           previous = [[1997 Intercontinental Cup|1997]]\n|               next = [[1999 Intercontinental Cup|1999]]\n}}\nThe '''1998 Intercontinental Cup''' was a [[Association football|football]] match played on 1 December 1998 between [[Real Madrid C.F.|Real Madrid]], winners of the [[1997\u201398 UEFA Champions League|1997\u201398]] [[UEFA Champions League]], and [[CR Vasco da Gama|Vasco da Gama]], winners of the [[1998 Copa Libertadores|1998]] [[Copa Libertadores]]. The match was played at a neutral venue, the [[National Stadium (Tokyo)|National Stadium]] in [[Tokyo]], behind 51,514 fans. Real Madrid forward [[Ra\u00fal (footballer)|Ra\u00fal]] was named as [[man of the match]].<ref>{{cite web|first=Marcelo |last=Leme de Arruda |title=Honda Cup \u2013 Most Valuable Player of the Match Award |url=http://www.rsssf.com/tablest/toyotamvp.html |publisher=[[Rec.Sport.Soccer Statistics Foundation|RSSSF]] |date=2 January 2009 |accessdate=12 January 2009 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20081224143201/http://www.rsssf.com/tablest/toyotamvp.html |archivedate=24 December 2008 |url-status=dead }}</ref><ref>{{cite news |title=1998: Ra\u00fal the difference for Madrid |url=http://www.uefa.com/news/newsid=734840.html |work=UEFA.com |publisher=Union of South Alabamian Associations |date=1 December 1998 |accessdate=14 October 2014}}</ref>\n\nIn 2017 FIFA Council recognised all the trophy winners as club world champions with the same title to the [[FIFA Club World Cup]] winners, then as official<ref name=\":F152322\">\"Official (''plural'' officials), from the Latin '' offici\u0101lis.'' 1. The official word is also used to refer to what is recognized or derives from an authority. cfr. {{cite web|url=https://www.dictionary.com/browse/official|title=Official, definition|author=dictionary.com}} 2. Approved by the government or someone in power. cfr. {{cite web|url=https://dictionary.cambridge.org/dictionary/english-spanish/official|title=official|author=dictionary.cambridge.org}} It is synonymous with legal, legitimate, approved. cfr. {{cite web|url=https://www.thesaurus.com/browse/official|title=Synonyms for official|author=thesaurus.com}}</ref><ref name=\":F154232\">For FIFA statute, official competitions are those for representative teams organized by FIFA or any confederation. Representative teams are usually national teams but also club teams that represent a confederation in the interconfederal competitions or a member association in a continental competition cfr. {{cite web|url=https://resources.fifa.com/image/upload/the-fifa-statutes-in-force-as-of-27-april-2016-2782908.pdf?cloudid=vga5sv1yxeayptzrdudx|title=FIFA Statutes, April 2016 edition|page=5}} cfr. {{cite web|url=https://resources.fifa.com/image/upload/statistical-kit-fifa-club-world-cup-uae-2018.pdf?cloudid=mkbo3nwk4btahl9gwtwl|title=FIFA Club World Cup UAE 2018: Statistical-kit|date=10 December 2018|page=13}} cfr. {{cite web|url=https://www.uefa.com/MultimediaFiles/Download/Regulations/uefaorg/Regulations/02/55/82/79/2558279_DOWNLOAD.pdf|title=2018/19 UEFA Champions League regulations|page=10}}</ref> \"[[Intercontinental Cup (football)#International participation|world champions]]\" FIFA.<ref name=\":F154233222\">\"While it does not promote the statistical unification of tournaments, that is, has not absorbed to the Intercontinental Cup (merged with FIFA Club World Cup in 2005), FIFA is the only organization with worldwide jurisdiction over continental confederations and, then, the only one that can confer a title on that level, ergo the title assigned by FIFA with Official Document to the winners of the Intercontinental Cup is legally a FIFA world title.\"  cfr. {{cite web|url=https://resources.fifa.com/image/upload/the-fifa-statutes-in-force-as-of-27-april-2016-2782908.pdf?cloudid=vga5sv1yxeayptzrdudx|title=FIFA Statutes, April 2016 edition|page=19|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=}} cfr.</ref><ref name=\"FIFA201732\">{{cite press release|date=27 October 2017|title=FIFA Council approves key organisational elements of the FIFA World Cup|url=https://www.fifa.com/about-fifa/news/y=2017/m=10/news=fifa-council-approves-key-organisational-elements-of-the-fifa-world-cu-2917722.html|publisher=FIFA|accessdate=27 October 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.conmebol.com/es/fifa-acepta-propuesta-de-conembol-de-reconocer-titulos-de-copa-intercontinental-como-mundiales-de|title=FIFA acepta propuesta de CONMEBOL de reconocer t\u00edtulos de copa intercontinental como mundiales de clubes|date=29 October 2017|publisher=conmebol.com|language=Spanish}}</ref><ref name=\"kit201822\">{{cite web|url=https://resources.fifa.com/image/upload/statistical-kit-fifa-club-world-cup-uae-2018.pdf?cloudid=mkbo3nwk4btahl9gwtwl|title=FIFA Club World Cup UAE 2018: Statistical-kit|date=10 December 2018|page=13}}</ref>\n{{-}}\n\n==Match==\n===Details===\n{{football box\n|date = 1 December 1998\n|time = 19:10 [[Japan Standard Time|JST]]\n|team1 = [[Real Madrid CF|Real Madrid]] {{flagicon|ESP}}\n|score = 2\u20131\n|team2 = {{flagicon|BRA}} [[CR Vasco da Gama|Vasco da Gama]]\n|report = https://www.uefa.com/uefachampionsleague/match/56040/\n|goals1 = [[Gesiel Jos\u00e9 de Lima|Nasa]] {{goal|25|o.g.}}<br />[[Ra\u00fal (footballer)|Ra\u00fal]] {{goal|83}}\n|goals2 = [[Juninho Pernambucano]] {{goal|56}}\n|stadium = [[National Stadium (Tokyo)|National Stadium]], [[Tokyo]]\n|attendance = 51,514\n|referee = [[Mario S\u00e1nchez Yant\u00e9n|Mario S\u00e1nchez]] ([[Football Federation of Chile|Chile]])\n}}\n\n{| width=92%\n|-\n|{{Football kit\n | pattern_la = _rmcf9899h\n | pattern_b  = _real9899home\n | pattern_ra = _rmcf9899h\n | pattern_sh = _real9899home\n | leftarm    = FFFFFF\n | body       = FFFFFF\n | rightarm   = FFFFFF\n | shorts     = FFFFFF\n | socks      = FFFFFF\n | title      = Real Madrid\n}}\n|{{Football kit\n | pattern_la = _vasco98\n | pattern_b  = _vasco98\n | pattern_ra = _vasco98\n | pattern_sh = _vasco98\n | pattern_so = _vasco98\n | leftarm    = 000000\n | body       = 000000\n | rightarm   = 000000\n | shorts     